# Testing And CI

- Prefer deterministic tests that use fixtures, mocks, or checked-in sample documents instead of live third-party dependencies.
- Keep GitHub Actions fast and readable with explicit setup, cache, and validation steps.
- When contracts change, update both app tests and workflow expectations.
- Do not weaken CI by skipping lint, typecheck, or test gates without explicit approval.
- Document any new env vars or external services required by CI.
